12 An Act relating to medical marijuana; amending 63
O.S. 2021, Sections 427.10, as amended by Section 12,
13 Chapter 251, O.S.L. 2022 and 427.13, as last amended
by Section 25, Chapter 182, O.S.L. 2024 (63 O.S.
14 Supp. 2024, Sections 427.10 and 427.13), which relate
to the Oklahoma Medical Marijuana and Patient
15 Protection Act; providing name of agency; requiring
creation and maintenance of certain registry;
16 providing certain educational requirements for
inclusion on the registry; requiring promulgation of
17 certain rules; allowing certain licensure boards to
develop or identify list of medical education
18 courses; providing time limitation for issuing
requests for proposals for a seed-to-sale tracking
19 system; authorizing multiyear or annual contracts;
providing list of requirements for the seed-to-sale
20 inventory tracking system; requiring agreed upon
contract terms if selected vendor utilizes
21 proprietary software for radio frequency
identification tags; and declaring an emergency.
